<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9567&amp;p=142371#p142371"><![CDATA[
jedahan in #nesdev pointed me to a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pkr2uv9X-8k" class="postlink">video of Steam's flower in action</a>, as well as describing how to make flower work on an NES controller. Instead of A, B, X, and Y, as one might do with a Super NES or bigger controller, one might use B, BB, A, and AA. Then A, B, Select, and Start for space, backspace, page change, and accept.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Mar 03, 2015 5:28 pm</p><hr />
