<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2012-12-03T17:17:41-07:00</updated>
<published>2012-12-03T17:17:41-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9567&amp;p=104003#p104003</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9567&amp;p=104003#p104003"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Text entry flower]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9567&amp;p=104003#p104003"><![CDATA[
Steam's new <a href="http://www.examiner.com/article/steam-big-picture-mode-launches-today-takes-on-consoles-with-minimalist-ui" class="postlink">Big Picture</a> front-end for home theater PCs introduces the flower, a text input method designed for gamepads. Eight groups of four letters are arranged in a circle. Pressing and releasing a direction or long-pressing it moves the cursor; holding a direction and pressing a button enters that letter corresponding to the button's position within the direction's group.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">,-------+-------+-------.<br />|   \   |   B   |   F   |<br />| ;   &amp; | A   C | E   G |<br />|   _   |   D   |   H   |<br />+-------+-------+-------+<br />|   Z   |       |   J   |<br />| Y   ? |       | I   K |<br />|   !   |       |   L   |<br />+-------+-------+-------+<br />|   V   |   R   |   N   |<br />| U   W | Q   S | M   O |<br />|   X   |   T   |   P   |<br />`-------+-------+-------'<br />L: Capital     R: Numbers<br /></div><br />For example, on the Super NES, you'd type &quot;assembly&quot; as Up+Y, Down+A, Down+A, Up+Right+Y, Down+Right+Y, Up+X, Right+B, Left+Y. But I wonder how to adapt it to something like the NES that has fewer convenient buttons.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Dec 03, 2012 5:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
